  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Uncertainty quantification was performed across inlet flow rate, rotational speed, and blood viscosity using a Latin hypercube sampling approach (N=200 samples); a screening sensitivity study based on Sobol indices was conducted internally and is summarized in the UQ report narrative, confirming that rotational speed accounts for approximately 61% of hemolysis index variance. Structured linkage of the sensitivity analysis artifact is pending final repository ingestion.",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "hasUncertaintyQuantification": true,
