      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs documented with sources and nominal values; input uncertainty ranges defined for UQ study; no undocumented free parameters.",
      "rationale": "Thirteen model inputs identified and documented: inlet flow rate, rotational speed, outlet pressure, blood viscosity parameters (four Carreau-Yasuda coefficients), hemolysis model constants (two), wall roughness, pump-rotor gap tolerance (three dimensions). Nominal values and uncertainty ranges sourced from manufacturer specifications and published literature. UQ sampling distributions assigned to all uncertain inputs; a screening sensitivity study using first-order Sobol indices was conducted and summarized in the UQ technical report, identifying rotational speed and hemolysis model exponent as dominant contributors. Structured sensitivity analysis artifact link pending repository finalization."
